        <p>
         <span style="color: #000000">
          Last week we celebrated my husbands 33rd birthday!
         </span>
        </p>
        <p>
         <span style="color: #000000">
          We are finally the same age now. Kinda sucks when youre the older one, even if it is only 3 months! But, I always liked them younger  3 months, or 3 years, does not make a difference to me.
          <img alt="Smile" class="wlEmoticon wlEmoticon-smile" src="http://cf.diethood.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/wlEmoticon-smile.png" style="border-style: none"/>
         </span>
        </p>
        <p>
         <span style="color: #000000">
          Back to hubz.
         </span>
        </p>
        <p>
         <span style="color: #000000">
          When I asked him about his birthday cake, without hesitation, he answered; Chocolate! As if I didnt know, but still, you have to ask. What else would a chocoholic want?
         </span>
        </p>
        <p>
         <span style="color: #000000">
          It didnt take me long to figure out which chocolate cake I was going to make for him.
         </span>
        </p>
        <p>
         <a href="http://cf.diethood.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/DSC02509.jpg">
          <span style="color: #000000">
           <img alt="chocolate olive oil cake" border="0" height="457" src="http://cf.diethood.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/DSC02509_thumb.jpg" style="margin: 0px 0px 2px;padding-left: 0px;padding-right: 0px;padding-top: 0px;border-width: 0px" title="chocolate olive oil cake" width="504"/>
          </span>
         </a>
        </p>
        <p>
         <span style="color: #000000">
          Few weeks ago, as I was reading through my friends blogs, I came across
         </span>
         <a href="http://www.morethanamountfull.com/" target="_blank">
          <span style="color: #000000">
           Chef Dennis
          </span>
         </a>
         <span style="color: #000000">
          recipe and photos of this gorgeous
         </span>
         <a href="http://www.morethanamountfull.com/2011/04/chocolate-olive-oil-cake-vintage-recipe.html" target="_blank">
          <span style="color: #000000">
           Chocolate Olive Oil Cake
          </span>
         </a>
         <span style="color: #000000">
          . As soon as I saw it, I bookmarked it with my husbands birthday on my mind. I knew he was going to love it, and love it he (we) did! This cake was delicious!
         </span>
        </p>
        <p>
         <span style="color: #000000">
          I took note of the Chefs suggestion  whipped cream filling  and got to work.
         </span>
        </p>
        <p>
         <span style="color: #000000">
          <strong>
           Chocolate Olive Oil Cake
          </strong>
         </span>
        </p>
        <p>
         <span style="color: #000000">
          <em>
           You will need:
          </em>
         </span>
        </p>
        <p>
         <span style="color: #000000">
          <strong>
           For the Cake
          </strong>
         </span>
        </p>
        <ul>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           3 Cups All Purpose Flour
          </span>
         </li>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           2 cups sugar
          </span>
         </li>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           6 tablespoons cocoa
          </span>
         </li>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           2 teaspoons baking soda
          </span>
         </li>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
            teaspoon salt
          </span>
         </li>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           3/4 cup Extra Virgin Olive Oil
          </span>
         </li>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           2 tablespoons white vinegar
          </span>
         </li>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           1 tablespoon vanilla extract
          </span>
         </li>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           2 cups cold water
          </span>
         </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
         <span style="color: #000000">
          <em>
           Directions:
          </em>
         </span>
        </p>
        <ul>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           Preheat the oven to 350.
          </span>
         </li>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           In a large mixing bowl sift together the flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
          </span>
         </li>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           Set the bowl to the mixer and with your mixer on low speed, pour in the oil, vinegar, vanilla, and water; beat until smooth.
          </span>
         </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
         <a href="http://cf.diethood.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/DSC02503.jpg">
          <span style="color: #000000">
           <img alt="chocolate cake batter" border="0" height="409" src="http://cf.diethood.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/DSC02503_thumb.jpg" style="margin: 0px 0px 2px;padding-left: 0px;padding-right: 0px;padding-top: 0px;border-width: 0px" title="chocolate cake batter" width="504"/>
          </span>
         </a>
        </p>
        <ul>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           Pour the mixture into two 9 pans coated with butter and dusted with flour.
          </span>
         </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
         <a href="http://cf.diethood.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/DSC02501.jpg">
          <span style="color: #000000">
           <img alt="flour dusted pan" border="0" height="414" src="http://cf.diethood.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/DSC02501_thumb.jpg" style="margin: 0px 0px 2px;padding-left: 0px;padding-right: 0px;padding-top: 0px;border-width: 0px" title="flour dusted cake pan" width="504"/>
          </span>
         </a>
        </p>
        <ul>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           Bake for 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean.
          </span>
         </li>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           Put the cake pans on cooling racks and cool for 15 to 20 minutes before removing the cakes from the pans to cool completely.
          </span>
         </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
         <a href="http://cf.diethood.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/DSC02508.jpg">
          <span style="color: #000000">
           <img alt="chocolate olive oil cake" border="0" height="427" src="http://cf.diethood.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/DSC02508_thumb.jpg" style="margin: 0px 0px 2px;padding-left: 0px;padding-right: 0px;padding-top: 0px;border-width: 0px" title="chocolate olive oil cake" width="504"/>
          </span>
         </a>
        </p>
        <ul>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           In the meantime, prepare the whipped cream filling and the mocha glaze.
          </span>
         </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
         <span style="color: #000000">
          <strong>
           For the Whipped Cream
          </strong>
         </span>
        </p>
        <ul>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           2 cups whipping cream
          </span>
         </li>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           1 teaspoon pure vanilla extract
          </span>
         </li>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           2 tablespoons sugar
          </span>
         </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
         <span style="color: #000000">
          <em>
           Directions:
          </em>
         </span>
        </p>
        <ul>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           Combine the whipping cream, vanilla, and sugar.
          </span>
         </li>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           Cover and chill in the refrigerator for 30 minutes.
          </span>
         </li>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           When chilled, beat the mixture until stiff peaks form.
          </span>
         </li>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           Spread the whipped cream over one of the cakes, then set the other cake on top.
          </span>
         </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
         <span style="color: #000000">
          <strong>
           For the Mocha Glaze
          </strong>
         </span>
        </p>
        <ul>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           2 tablespoons powdered instant espresso
          </span>
         </li>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
            cup boiling water
          </span>
         </li>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           1  cups heavy cream
          </span>
         </li>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           2 tablespoons light corn syrup
          </span>
         </li>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           2 2/3 cups finely chopped dark chocolate
          </span>
         </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
         <span style="color: #000000">
          <em>
           Directions:
          </em>
         </span>
        </p>
        <ul>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           Stir together the instant espresso and boiling water until smooth. Set aside.
          </span>
         </li>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           Combine the cream and the corn syrup in a heavy saucepan and bring to a boil over medium heat.
          </span>
         </li>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           Remove the pan from the heat and stir in the espresso.
          </span>
         </li>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           Pour the mixture over the chocolate and let sit, covered, for 2 to 3 minutes.
          </span>
         </li>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           Stir until the chocolate is completely melted and the sauce is very smooth.
          </span>
         </li>
         <li>
          <span style="color: #000000">
           Keep warm until ready to use, then pour it over the cake.
          </span>
         </li>
        </ul>
